{"abstract": "In the first half of the year, the market richly rewarded investors in many companies with weak balance sheets \u2014 those with relatively high debt loads.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/07/business/mutfund/when-weak-balance-sheets-outperform-the-strong.html", "snippet": "In the first half of the year, the market richly rewarded investors in many companies with weak balance sheets \u2014 those with relatively high debt loads.", "lead_paragraph": "MANU DAFTARY, manager of the Quaker Strategic Growth fund, says he learned a valuable lesson in 2009. He avoided companies like the American International Group, Bank of America and Citgroup, which, to one degree or another, were damaged by the subprime mortgage crisis and benefited from the help of the Federal Reserve. His portfolio\u2019s performance suffered, though, as he minimized investments in such companies.", "print_section": "BU", "print_page": "16", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/07/07/business/07-BALANCE1/07-BALANCE1-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 379, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/07/07/business/07-BALANCE1/07-BALANCE1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 379}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/07/07/business/07-BALANCE1/07-BALANCE1-jumbo.jpg", "height": 647, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/07/07/business/07-BALANCE1/07-BALANCE1-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1293, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/07/07/business/07-BALANCE